compile:

g++ build3Dmodel_v1.23.cpp -o build3Dmodel


+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

======
Usage:
======

[wangsheng@cruncher RaptorX_Util]$ ./build3Dmodel
Version: 1.23
Usage:
===================================================================
./build3Dmodel -i fasta_file -q query_name
        [ -d pdb_root] [ -m mod_bin ] [ -n mod_num ] [ -k keep_file ]
-------------------------------------------------------------------
 -i fasta_file:  the input alignment file in fasta format.
 -q query_name:  the name of the query protein.
 [-d pdb_root]:  the folder containing the PDB file of the template.
                 (default = databases/pdb_BC100/ )
 [-m mod_bin]:   the MODELLER executable file,
                 (default = ~/bin/modeller9v8/bin/mod9v8 )
 [-n mod_num]:   the number of 3D models to be generated
                 from the alignment (default=1)
 [-k keep_file]: keep temporary files (default=0, not keep)
===================================================================


Note that MODELLER 9v8 should be installed in ~/bin/modeller9v8 as default
